<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Spill" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Spill</orth> (impf. and partic. <emph>spilled</emph> or <emph>spilt</emph>) 1) to shed; once used of tears: <bibl n="shak. luc 1236" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1236</bibl>. Usually of blood: <bibl n="shak. ven 1167" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 999" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 999</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 999" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 999</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.115" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 125</bibl> (Ff <emph>spent</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 3.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.8.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 8, 3</bibl>.<lb />2) to destroy: <cit><quote>so full of artless jealousy is guilt, it --s itself in fearing to be spilt,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>crack nature's moulds, all germens s. at once,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. luc 1801" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1801</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.115" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 115</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>